  "Sanction Details" : "SEC LITIGATION RELEASE 20779, OCTOBER 14, 2008: SEC ANNOUNCED THAT THE DISTRICT COURT ENTERED FINAL JUDGMENT AS TO DEFENDANT ON OCTOBER 9, 2008.  WITHOUT ADMITTING OR DENYING THE ALLEGATIONS, DEFENDANT CONSENTED TO THE JUDGMENT AND ORDERED TO PAY DISGORGEMENT, PREJUDMENT INTEREST AND POST JUDGMENT INTEREST IN THE AMOUNTS OF $7,157.60, $1,383.17 AND $73.41, AND A CIVIL PENALTY OF $7,230.41.  DEFENDANT MUST SATISFY PAYMENT OF THESE AMOUNTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH A PAYMENT SCHEDULE.  FURTHER, DEFENDANT WAS ENJOINED FROM FUTURE VIOLATIONS OF SECTIONS 10(B) AND 14(E) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 AND RULES 10B-5 AND 14E-3 THEREUNDER."
